-- Ghana Lawmakers Approve $850 Million Loan From China, Times Says
-- B y   M o s e s   M o z a r t   D z a w u
-- 2012-02-24T09:59:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-24/ghana-lawmakers-approve-850-million-loan-from-china-times-says.html
Ghana ’s parliament approved an
agreement to borrow $850 million from  China Development Bank  for
natural-gas infrastructure in the country’s western region, the
Ghanaian Times reported.  Projects include the construction of a gas-processing plant
and an offshore submarine pipeline to deliver the fuel to it,
the Accra-based newspaper said, citing James Klutse Avedzi,
chairman of the joint committee on finance and mines.  The facility forms part of a $3 billion loan agreement that
 Ghana  signed with the Chinese bank for infrastructure expansion,
the Times said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 